caption: They serve buffet lunch every Friday and Sunday.  One can enjoy best meals, fantastic ambiance.

Staffs and management  had simply the proper balance of friendliness and efficiency. Kudos! The lattes were excellent as well. The vibe here is part of the fun- I was just in Italy a few months ago- and this felt like I was back.
They start you with some delicious treats which is almost enough to have for dinner. Amazingly fresh and tasty treats! I had the octopus salad which was perfectly tender and, again, almost too much.
Simply, the best!

This is the place for real authentic Roman Italian. Try the veal parmigiana - incredible. All the dishes are equal. Start out with the seafood salad - this place is it. Daughter lives in Chicago so we visit quite often. Always like trying new places and we found this Gem!! Family owned, great customer service and the food is excellent. On our visits to the city we make sure we stop in and enjoy a exquisite meal.

Waited outside in the cold for 45 minutes after my pickup time to receive my order. Was not told to go home and come back later or offered to wait inside. Kept being told “one minute”. We used to order here all the time but going to take it off the list.
This place rocks!
My favorite location for Italian food. Super delicious. It has a great feel to it.

Delicious food and they do a wonderful job with gluten free. We’ve eaten here several times and last time we did pick up I had the baby with me and they saw me get out of my car with the baby, grabbed my food, and ran it out to me so I didn’t have to come all the way in. Staff is beyond kind and accommodating.

Was not a fan of the way the owner Ramone Aguirre insulted me and made fun of me.  Like he said, he could care less.  I wish him luck with his business but with this kind of personal attacks during working hours, I can see he has less time to serve and more time facebook attacking when he should be managing.  Best of luck with that business strategy over the long run

In a city full of fantastic restaurants, for years, this is our absolute favorite for Italian.  The owner is there every night and the excellent wait staff have been with him for years.  With artistically painted high ceilings, yet an intimate, low-key atmosphere, this a perfect date night spot for dinner or drinks, or even small groups.  The pasta is made in-house and the sauces each have exquisitely balanced flavors.  The chicken is always tender and delicious and the breads are always fresh.  Make sure to end your meal by enjoying the BEST tiramisu in all of Chicago!  Also, the portions are LARGE, so be prepared to share or take home tasty leftovers.
Very well done Italian dishes.  Generous portions and a good value.  Love this place.
Bella Notte is an old school Italian staple in Chicago -- I've been a fan for over 20 years...the food is always consistent, fresh and delicious!
Very good food and very clean
Best Italian food in Chicago! Very couterous staff.
Good food, but our waiter who was also the bartender wasn’t wearing his mask, which was around his neck, at all. Other servers were; it was pretty disappointing.
Outstanding food. Traditional Italian. Do yourself a favor and try it out.

Ordered delicious take out. We might have ordered more than we could handle but we are happy to have leftovers for a couple days. The pasta and salad were of a great quality and we can’t wait to try out other things on the menu.
Always amazing. Very friendly staff and some tremendous food. :)

We ordered a three course meal for our “lockdown” anniversary and Bella Notte did not disappoint. We ordered the calamari and antipasti to share for our starter which arrived with a wonderful loaf of bread that was still wonderfully soft and warm (and even had the cocktail sauce, fresh sliced lemons and butter portions included). Our mains were Chicken Saltimboca which my husband wolfed down with a side of penne with a marinara sauce that tasted so fresh of tomato; I had the carbonara and we shared a side of garlic sautéed broccoli which was equally tasty. Our dessert was then two wonderful portions of their tiramisu - perfectly light and fluffy. The portions are incredibly generous and gave us plenty for lunch the next day too (and they were still just as nice as the night before!) We had a lovely dinner on a special evening, despite the lockdown, and want to thank the restaurant and staff for making our evening so wonderful - we will definitely be visiting in person soon - thank you.

Bella Notte is open for take outs and delivery. I just had one the best pepper and egg sandwiches I ever had! Came with some homemade chips. Got a good bottle of their house wine too. What more can you ask for! (Their full menu is available)
Fantastic food. Their service is horrible. Called multiple times. Put on hold multiple times. And even hung up on.
Better than average italian restaurant.
Great atmosphere nice people great food

This Italian bistro was a great experience. The Farfalle and crumbled Italian sausage is fuqing amazing! Everything was very fresh and tasty. The portions are nicely sized. Staff is friendly. Prices are reasonable. Romantic ambiance. Cozy seating; Could be a good thing or bad thing but personally the seating is too close. Valet parking recommended, its $14. Great wine selection. I wanted a specific wine from the menu but they were out. House wine was all they had. Ooooowee that house wine tasted like Wal-Mart Oakleaf wine. Wasn't very good. Everything else was fantastic.

Long lived Italian restaurant with good reason. The food is great. Old school dishes from veal to chicken to pasta, everything is prepared fresh. Baked clams are super as are sausage and peppers and grilled calamar for appetizers. Linguini with clams could have served four. All chicken dishes were fork tender and some come in smaller portions. Carrot cake and Italian cookies ended the evening on a sweet note. Service is friendly and efficient and the high ceilinged old room brings back a bygone era. A bit off the beaten path but with the drive/uber.
One of best Italian restaurants in the hood clams fresh pasta cooked perfect
Excellent food with huge portions!
The food was amazing
Had dinner here not too long ago and the food was delicious and the atmosphere was great! Will definitely dine here again.
Very nice place
Wonderful food! I had the brushetta and chicken marsala. Great service as well!

Typical Italo-American restaurant with massive portions, friendly faces and neo-roman décor throughout.  Our rotini all'arrabiata fed the two of us and we had leftovers. Escarole.amd Rapini nice and garlicky, sautéed to perfection. Comfort food as la mamma intended it.
Fantastic place! Generous portions for a fair price. The food and service was great!
Loved my food! Would definitely come back
Beautiful little restaurant in west town!! The food is outstanding!!

This is an outstanding restaurant. Food was delicious, and all staff were friendly and helpful. We ordered the large portions which were well worth the price!  We had plenty of food to take home for yet another serving. We will return for sure!  Highly recommend.
Absolutely delicious! Food came quickly and my water glass was never empty. Definitely impressed.
Quiet restaurant with great food and service! We enjoyed a great business dinner there with minimum disruptions during our conversations.

Four of us ate on a quiet Tuesday evening. Service was very slow for being one of two tables.. although the gentlemen serving was friendly enough. Food portions are large but lacking in meat... Food was average tasting. Unsure why the venue so dimly lit... Overall an average experience..
A wonderful restaurant... it's elegant and everything on the menu is homemade! Come hungry because the portions are generous!

Service, drinks & food were delicious. Our children had butter noodles and they were the best I’ve ever had. The texture, flavor & portion were sinful! Such rich flavor. I can’t remember the name of the dish I had but it had noodles peas mushrooms prosciutto and a white cream sauce that was the thickest yet creamiest I’ve ever had. The cosmopolitans wear a nice size chilled perfection and delicious. For dessert we had carrot cake tiramisu and chocolate chip cheesecake. Espresso, coffee and after dinner drinks were magical ending to this fantastic meal. I highly recommend this place.
Some of the best italian in Chicago! Everything’s great and the huge portions make the best leftovers. Service is incredible
Comfortable family setting. Great food and service. Order half order on pasta dishes

A Chicago landmark  for Italian food. The food is always amazing, authentic and delicious. The staff is friendly and helpful. Most of them have been there for 20 years or more. You get consistent excellence.
The restaurant was fantastic! Food delicious and service was excellent! Highly recommend it. Wonderful place for date night.
italian food and service here is great. This place is absolutely one of my favorites. The staff was sociable and attentive.
italian food, very satisfying. One of the best spots of its kind in the area. Prices were decent.
italian food, mmm, so good. Came in on a Weds.
My father and I went to dinner last night and everything was excellent! The food was delicious and the service was impeccable! We’re definitely going to visit again the next time we’re in town!
Great food with generous portions. Service was excellent, too.
The food was excellent and also the service
Service was slow. Food is always good but felt ignored.
Good food and good service.  Definitely going back
Great food, nice Martinis

We didn't make any reservations but we stopped by since we've been here before.  The place has plenty of paintings from Italy and reminded me of the last trip I made there.  The man at the entrance walked us over to our table and our server came right away to give us the specials of the day.  We got some drinks and they were great,  not too much or too little alcohol. And as for the food, it was good and plenty for more than one person per plate.  Later on when it started to get dark outside, the candles on the rabble were lit.  Our server was bilingual since he spoke English and Spanish. The place can host small to large groups,  I saw a table being set up for a party of 13. Try the drinks and share the plates.
The best as always. Great service phenomenal food, strong drinks, great wine. My favorite place to visit thanks Ramon for always going over the top.
Such great food! The restaurant was able to accommodate our party of 12 without fail. The food portions were rather large and very tasty.
Excellent food courteous and timely service.
Great Italian food!
italian food and the feeling at this location is great. I will probably become a regular. Prices are fair.
Excellent place for quality Italian food. This place does it for me. Looking forward to returning with my relatives. Similar to a place in Denver I liked.
Delicious eggplant parm!
Solid neighborhood Italian eatery.  Foods are reasonably well prepared but not destinative.  Not a destination but good option for a casual evening out with family and friends.
One of the BEST tasting Eggplant Parmigiana in the city.
The food is just wonderful. It's family style so come hungry.
great place, very prompt service, option to choose full or half plates,
Worst customer service by Ramon, which he said was the owner. If the owner treats customers like he does, I'll take my business elsewhere.
Old school Italian, good food and service. 1/2 portions are a nice option.
Great service and awesome food.
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. All of the food my group had was amazing. I will be back.
I really like it there wen I go to eat actually my dad is one of the chef that cooks there

Great cold seafood salad appetizer.  Every pasta is excellent.  Green Noodles Alforno best I have had. Courteous and friendly waitstaff. Thinly sliced and lightly breaded Veal Picante one of my favorites. Valet available.

This place was fantastic!! The lights are set low, so if you’re looking for a romantic setting, this is a good place. The portions are large - I ordered the full size fettuccini alfredo and have enough food for at least two more meals. The alfredo sauce was the best I’ve ever had! I would recommend the fried calamari as well. I’ll definitely be back!
The service was good and the food was good
Great food. Plan to slow down and enjoy good wine and great company.   Solid Chicago stop!

The decor is nice and has low lighting for a relaxed scene. The staff was extremely nice and made sure we were always taken care of. The food was really good. I ordered basic spaghetti in meat sauce in the full size. The full size is meant for about 2-3 people. I had tons of leftovers. I also tried the carrot cake and it was really good! The frosting tasted like Cinnabon frosting. I would definitely come back here!
Love this place. Food always excellent. Decor very welcoming. Wait staff friendly and takes great care.
always great food and fantastic service!
Great food off the beaten track in Chicago

Good Service, great atmosphere in the heart of West Loop. Portions are generous and probably one of the best places for 5 star Italian food. Check out the valet services, especially if you take the journey during the winter!
Food and service was outstanding.

Well we did the linguine with shrimp and broccoli. Only issue is the shrimp were way over cooked and the broccoli was as well. And there really was no garlic in the dish as listed. Very underwhelming. On the bright side, the bread was pretty good and seemed to be made in house.
You can't beat this place for the price! Food is incredible and service is superb!

I was disappointed in the rush service. As if they were rushing us out to close. And when it came time for the bill the poor attitude cashier , so called manager took his time to accept the gift cards we used to pay the bill. And wouldn’t let us leave until he finished clearing them.  Was not very polite and was unprofessional.  For italian food, There are plenty of better restaurants.  I will never go back.
Amazing service! Everyone was so attentive to every need! Good Italian food—amazing people! If you are in the area, give this place a try and you'll be delighted.
Always good.
Great Italian food!
Classical ethnic place. Excellent food. Portions on the larger side. Yes, food is a little opinionated. The staff is properly opinionated. They are properly proud of the place. Well worth returning.

I placed an order online just after 9pm tonight. The hours of the restaurant show until 11:30. After approximately 30 minutes of waiting my order is cancelled. I call the restaurant and was told that the owner closes early if they have a lot of catering orders and that it is "His restaurant, his hours". This is unacceptable customer service. I certainly expect more from a highly rated restaurant but I guess they were done working for the day so who cares if there were orders in queue already..
Just go there and eat no words on how good the food is.
Beautiful place, good service and best of all great food.
Delicious food! Nice ambiance.
Excellent food, service, and ambiance!  Recommend highly!  I shall return.
Just the best
Friendly service, and delicious large portions!

Probably my favorite Italian Restaurant in the whole city!!  Great food, sauce and atmosphere.  Huge portions and friendly staff.  Tends to fill up so plan ahead.  I live nearby and do carry out often.  Vodka Sauce or Shrimp Fra Diavlo are personal favorites.
Good food
Great food great location. Just a little cramped but overall great experience.

Have not been there in so long and was reminded that I should consider it more often, the food was good, service was outstanding, and it still hasn't changed because there were clearly old school Grand street regulars that know they are getting value along with overly generous portions. My wife agreed with me and that doesn't come often.

I have loved this place since it opened over 20 years ago. Ramon Junior is doing a great job of keeping the restaurant as consistent as it as ever been! My favorite stand by for Italian food in the downtown area.
Always great food and great service
I love their baby Stone Cherry baked clams. Great food great atmosphere. Very good prices say hi to Ramon for me.
Huge portions. Great food. Reasonably priced wine list.

It is a very terrible story , I was have dinner with my bf last night in this restaurant, our totally bill was $93 dollar  , I paid the $21 dollar good tips for the service ( waiter name is Dav) , however I forget  i left my purse there until tonight when I came home , I called my bf to called the restaurant , the person who answer the phone said it was nothing there , after 30 minutes I called it again the guy who answer the phone he said yes , it was behind the bar , they are close at 9 pm when we arrival there at 8:50pm , there is no more customers there , I saw the all people were come out sit together, when I open my purse the money cash all was gone , I talked the reception guy he said the purse was behind the bar all day , the bar guy said I didn't touch the purse , the purse just leave there , the waitress said he leave the purse to the bar since he found it when we left , I was so angry , I told the reception why my boyfriend first time called in then the guy who answered the phone said nothing and when I called he said yes , he answered me he sit there all days I can asked my boyfriend come to identify and have talked with him , we totally spent $93 dollar for dining order , I paid $21 tips to the waiter , his name is Dav. and I lost my under 100 cash in my purse , this is a black restaurant
Food is always excellent and so consistent.  Never a disappointment. We come from out of state for this place.
Great Italian eatery with excellent service.
Portions are ample and delicious.
Food was excellent and the service is outstanding. Great atmosphere. This restaurant is a winner. The prices are very reasonable for the large portions you get.
Great food and plenty of it.
Consistently delicious! One of our favorites.
All things top notch! The service was quick and friendly. The food was beyond delicious and the environment was right out of a movie. This is a great restaurant for a visit to Chicago :)
Brought a group of 12 people in for a bday dinner. Food and staff completely on point. So impressed with the level of service. Every pasta dish had its own uniqueness. True 5 stars

Tons of food. Full order feeds 4 comfortably. This is true Italian. It's all about the sauce. This isn't American Italian where it is packed with meat.  It is off the beaten path (still in safe neighborhood) but for an authentic Italian dinner it is worth it.
Great food and huge portions
Always a pleasure to eat with Bella Note. You  will not.be disappointed.
Hidden gem on Grand Avenue. Full on Italian restaurant. AWESOME catering too.
Stopped for lunch. Lovely interior and delicious food, but slow.
Food was good
Simply the BEST!!!

Top-notch home-style Italian food in a charming room with attentive service. The menu covers a lot of ground, from grilled meats to veal and chicken to red sauce pastas - and usually a few daily specials - but I'm regularly drawn to the grilled vegetable platter, the homemade 8-finger cavatelli with rapini (and garlic!), and the grilled calamari and octopus. Small but well-chosen wine list. 10-seat bar for waiting or solo dining - or for a quick drink at intermission of plays next door at Artistic Home. Party room upstairs. Valet parking. Convenient to United Center for pre-game dining. Warning: full portions of pastas are truly gargantuan and can easily feed two or three people. Half-portions are still large, but you can try two or three and make everyone at the table happy.

Look no further, don't hesitate, just go to this wonderful restaurant, the food is spectacular, the service is perfect, the veal was the best I had ever  eaten anywhere.  The Wedding Soup was fabulous, coffee was perfect and the staff better than most.  Polite, attentive and generous. WE will be back soon.
Fire Italian food! Enough said
Delicious and authentic Italian and great salads!
Great food, superb service....BEST in the neighborhood!!!
Tried many of the Chicago's best but this one still sticks out in my mind. Get the sausage and peppers for an appetizer and order anything else on the menu. It won't disappoint.
Best restaurant in chicago! Highly recommend!

Old school Italian with enormous portions. The service was kind of crappy, but the food was outstanding. Enough so it made up for the bad service. I'll be back despite the service because the food is worth it. They offer anything Italian your heart, ahem...belly desires.

Well made cocktails, excellent food (you can cut the veil with a fork), and a good atmosphere. I had a wonderful time with my gal and a few friends. The seating was roomy and comfortable. The staff is courteous and attentive. So much win on a snowy Saturday night.
Horrible greasy food, raw shrimps, no meat on the other dishes, got sick after eating there and was expensive.
Really good food
Love this place. true italian food at a reasonable price. The chef is passionate about what he does and the enviroment is great.

Was extremely unfriendly and unaccomidating for a reservation mistake. After it was discovered by the front desk host that our reservation wasn't submitted by the previous hostess when we called a few hours before, he simply rolled his eyes and told us it would be a couple minute wait. There were no apologies or even a sense of haste to seat us. Within the 45 minutes that we waited, we also witnessed two other smaller parties that had a similar reservation mistake, and the host gave a similar response to them as well. We ended up leaving due to the lack of warmth demonstrated by the person who was supposed to be greeting the guests. Overwhelmingly disappointed.
Some of the best Italian I have ever had in my life.  I come back as much as I can!

Great food, great prices, great service and a fantastic romantic setting. The owner Ramon is truly passionate about his business and it shows with its presentation. It inspires his staff to work hard and I had many memorable dinners at this place with my Husband. Top Notch

I would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking to go to North Beach for a meal. The menu is extensive so I will definitely be back again to try one of their other dishes. The owner/manager here is really amazing. Very nice and has great hospitality. The atmosphere and ambiance of being able to eat right is really cool. The food here is really good. Highly recommend this place.

Generous portions too! We loved the back patio for the privacy. We were very pleased with our delicious pasta dishes. Service was friendly and our water glasses were filled. I would highly recommend Belle Notte to anyone interested in hosting a private event. We loved our singing waiter too! The entire experience was Fantastic! Bravo! The food is good, and we will also be returning as regular guests!

When my boyfriend surprised me by taking me to dinner here, I was ecstatic! They gave us a table in the corner for us to have a little romantic dinner. The staff was extremely nice, and the food was incredibly delicious.  Thank you Bella Notte!

I never thought I could find a fine and inexpensive Italian restaurant like Bella Notte. The food is excellent and the service as well. I ordered seafood pasta and surprising I paid what in an another place I would pay for a sandwich. They make you feel at home. I recommend this restaurant if you are craving for a good Italian lunch.

Once again, Bella Notte Ristorante did not disappoint us. We had the beautiful and delicious handkerchief pasta with just the right amount of that yummy pesto sauce. Also tried the veal with the tomato and it was perfectly cooked (NOT overcooked at all), so good with just the right flavors. Highly recommended. Will be back again and again.

If you want home cooked Italian, this is your spot. It's spot on great delicious food. you can smell the garlic from around the corner. It's super homey and welcoming. It's a casual place and you can easily become a regular.
Best food around hands down.
Awesome Italian food and the service is fantastic. Very cozy and charming atmosphere.
Chicken sicillian...out of this world
